%20the%20speeding%20police%20patrol%20vehicle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20bodycam%20footage%20released%20by%20the%20Seattle%20Police%20Department%2C%20Officer%20Daniel%20Auderer%20laughed%20about%20the%20deadly%20crash%20and%20dismissed%20any%20implication%20Dave%20might%20be%20at%20fault%20or%20that%20a%20criminal%20investigation%20was%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKing%20County%20Prosecuting%20Attorney%20Leesa%20Manion%20said%20that%20she%20believes%20they%20lack%20the%20evidence%20to%20prove%20a%20criminal%20case%20beyond%20a%20reasonable%20doubt%2C%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20King%20County%20Prosecuting%20Attorney's%20Office%20to%20review%20all%20available%20evidence%20relating%20to%20the%20case%20involving%20Seattle%20Police%20Officer%20Kevin%20Dave%20and%20the%20January%202023%20collision%20death%20of%20Jaahnavi%20Kandula.%20After%20staffing%20this%20case%20with%20senior%20deputy%20prosecuting%20attorneys%20and%20office%20leadership%2C%20I%20have%20determined%20that%20we%20lack%20sufficient%20evidence%20under%20Washington%20State%20law%20to%20prove%20a%20criminal%20case%20beyond%20a%20reasonable%20doubt.%26quot%3B%20The%20statement%20also%20said%20that%20the%20prosecutor's%20office%20also%20finds%20the%20comments%20made%20by%20Seattle%20Police%20Officer%20Daniel%20Auderer%2C%20recorded%20on%20his%20body-worn%20video%2C%20%26quot%3Bappalling%20and%20deeply%20troubling.%26quot%3B%20Auderer%2C%20who%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20January%20collision%2C%20was%20captured%20in%20the%20video%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BBut%20she%20is%20dead%26quot%3B%20and%20laughing%20while%20on%20the%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20was%2026%20anyway%2C%26quot%3B%20Auderer%20said%20in%20the%20video.%20%26quot%3BShe%20had%20limited%20value.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BOfficer%20Auderer's%20comments%20were%20also%20unprofessional%20and%20undermined%20the%20public's%20trust%20in%20the%20Seattle%20Police%20Department%20and%20law%20enforcement%20in%20general%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Manion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20egregious%20as%20Officer%20Auderer's%20comments%20are%2C%20they%20do%20not%20change%20the%20PAO's%20legal%20analysis%20into%20the%20conduct%20of%20Officer%20Dave.%20It%20is%20the%20Office%20of%20Police%20Accountability%20that%20bears%20the%20responsibility%20of%20disciplinary%20investigation%20and%20proceedings%20relating%20to%20Officer%20Auderer's%20comment%2C%20not%20the%20PAO.%26quot%3B%20Auderer%20was%20pulled%20from%20patrol%20in%20September%202023%20and%20reassigned%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bnon-operational%20position.%26quot%3B%20Auderer%20could%20still%20be%20fired%20after%20the%20fallout%20of%20his%20insensitive%20comments%20captured%20on%20bodycam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAuderer's%20chain%20of%20command%20and%20the%20Office%20of%20Police%20Accountability%20(OPA)%20found%20he%20acted%20unprofessionally.%20For%20that%2C%20he%20faces%20the%20highest%20disciplinary%20range%20of%20nearly%20two%20weeks%20suspension%20up%20to%20termination%2C%20according%20to%20a%20disciplinary%20action%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20a%20final%20disciplinary%20decision%2C%20Auderer%20will%20have%20the%20chance%20to%20meet%20with%20Police%20Chief%20Adrian%20Diaz%20to%20disagree.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20disciplinary%20hearing%20is%20scheduled%20for%20March%204%2C%20K5%20News%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeattle%20local%20media%20reported%20that%20speed%20was%20the%20cause%20of%20the%20collision%2C%20as%20the%20speed%20at%20which%20Dave%20was%20travelling%20did%20%26quot%3Bnot%20allow%20(Kandula)%20or%20him%20sufficient%20time%20to%20detect%2C%20address%20and%20avoid%20a%20hazard%20that%20presented%20itself.%26quot%3B%20Dave%20was%20responding%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bpriority%20one%26quot%3B%20call%20at%20the%20request%20of%20the%20Seattle%20Fire%20Department%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Seattle%20Police%20Department.%20According%20to%20the%20police%20report%2C%20the%20officer%20was%20responding%20to%20a%20report%20of%20a%20drug%20overdose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20officer%20did%20not%20have%20his%20siren%20activated%20continuously.%20Instead%2C%20the%20officer%20%26quot%3Bchirped%26quot%3B%20his%20siren%20at%20the%20intersection.%20He%20did%20have%20his%20emergency%20lights%20on%2C%20according%20to%20a%20previous%20statement%20from%20the%20police%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20memo%20to%20Seattle%20police%2C%20prosecutors%20wrote%20there%20was%20not%20enough%20evidence%20to%20prove%20Dave%20showed%20%26quot%3Bconscious%20disregard%20for%20others%20safety.%26quot%3B%20A%20drug%20recognition%20expert%20responded%20to%20the%20scene%20and%20found%20no%20impairment%20in%20the%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKandula%20was%20a%20graduate%20student%20at%20Northeastern%20University%20at%20the%20Seattle%20campus.%20The%20university%20said%20in%20January%202023%20that%20they%20would%20award%20her%20degree%20posthumously%20and%20present%20it%20to%20her%20family.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708567560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2F9l726dfg_jaahnavi-kandula_625x300_14_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Fjaahnavi-kandulas-death-us-cop-who-ran-over-indian-student-to-not-face-criminal-charges-5103644%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Seattle%20police%20officer%20who%20struck%20and%20killed%20Indian%20student%20Jaahnavi%20Kandula%20while%20responding%20to%20an%20overdose%20call%2C%20will%20not%20face%20any%20criminal%20charges%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20%26quot%3Bsufficient%26quot%3B%20evidence%2C%20authorities%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Fjaahnavi-kandulas-death-us-cop-who-