how-to-fight-13077055%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Russia%20Has%20Never%20Hurt%20India%20Interests'%3A%20Jaishankar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F29133605%2FFzuFHifXoAIWH-o.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20External%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20has%20said%20of%20the%20Indo-Russian%20relations%20that%20as%20far%20as%20independent%20India%20was%20concerned%2C%20%E2%80%9CRussia%20has%20never%20hurt%20our%20interests%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20this%20when%20asked%20by%20the%20German%20newspaper%20%3Cem%3EHandelsblatt%3C%2Fem%3E%20if%20India%E2%80%99s%20purchase%20of%20Russian%20oil%20was%20a%20burden%20on%20its%20relationship%20with%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEveryone%20conducts%20a%20relationship%20based%20on%20their%20past%20experiences.%20If%20I%20look%20at%20the%20history%20of%20India%20post-independence%2C%20Russia%20has%20never%20hurt%20our%20interests%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jaishankar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20relations%20of%20powers%20like%20Europe%2C%20the%20US%2C%20China%20or%20Japan%20with%20Russia%2C%20they%20have%20all%20seen%20ups%20and%20downs.%20We%20have%20had%20a%20stable%20and%20always%20very%20friendly%20relationship%20with%20Russia.%20And%20our%20relationship%20with%20Russia%20today%20is%20based%20on%20this%20experience.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Findias-import-dependency-on-oil-and-gas-to-surpass-80-by-fy28%2Farticle67154624.ece%5C%22%3Edependent%20on%20oil%20imports%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0as%20its%20domestic%20oil%20output%20lags%20behind%20growing%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20purchased%20oil%20from%20Russia%20at%20cheaper%20prices%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20cut%20its%20oil%20import%20bill%2C%20taking%20advantage%20of%20discounted%20prices%20owing%20to%20Western%20sanctions%20starting%20in%20early%202022%20as%20a%20result%20of%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20government%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-russian-oil-jaishankar-sergei-lavrov%5C%22%3Edefended%20its%20decision%20to%20defy%20the%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20arguing%20it%20had%20a%20duty%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20lower%20prices%20whenever%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20reiterated%20this%20stance%20in%20his%20interview%20to%C2%A0%3Cem%3EHandelsblatt%3C%2Fem%3E%20when%20asked%20if%20India%20and%20Europe%E2%80%99s%20differing%20relations%20with%20Russia%20%E2%80%9Cput%20a%20strain%20on%20India-Europe%20relations%E2%80%9D.%20The%20interview%20was%20conducted%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20Munich%20Security%20Conference%20he%20attended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20mentioned%20the%20energy%20issue.%20When%20the%20fighting%20started%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Europe%20shifted%20a%20large%20part%20of%20its%20energy%20procurement%20to%20the%20Middle%20East%20%E2%80%93%20until%20then%20the%20main%20supplier%20for%20India%20and%20other%20countries.%20What%20should%20we%20have%20done%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20many%20cases%2C%20our%20Middle%20East%20suppliers%20gave%20priority%20to%20Europe%20because%20Europe%20paid%20higher%20prices.%20Either%20we%20would%20have%20had%20no%20energy%20because%20everything%20would%20have%20gone%20to%20them.%20Or%20we%20would%20have%20ended%20up%20paying%20a%20lot%20more%20because%20you%20were%20paying%20more%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20he%20said%20that%20the%20global%20order%20is%20currently%20facing%20%E2%80%9Cmultiple%20kinds%20of%20stress%E2%80%9D.%20The%20stress%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Cshocks%E2%80%9D%20such%20as%20Covid%2C%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20NATO%20withdrawal%20from%20Afghanistan%20and%20disruptive%20climate%20events%20that%20are%20happening%20more%20and%20more%20frequently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20it%20is%20not%20just%20about%20strengthening%20the%20international%20order%2C%20but%20also%20about%20changing%20this%20order.%20Who%20shapes%20it%20and%20on%20what%20basis%3F%20The%20international%20order%20must%20evolve%20further%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20proposed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20it%20further%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CTake%20the%20United%20Nations%20as%20an%20important%20part%20of%20the%20international%20order.%20The%20UN%20started%20with%2050%20members%2C%20now%20it%20has%20almost%20200%20%E2%80%93%20but%20the%20management%20of%20the%20UN%20has%20not%20changed.%20The%20group%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20top%2020%20or%2030%20economies%20has%20changed%20a%20lot%20in%20the%20past%20two%20decades.%20Ten%20years%20ago%2C%20India%20was%20the%20eleventh%20largest%20economy%2C%20now%20we%20are%20number%20five.%20In%20a%20few%20years%2C%20we%20will%20be%20the%20third%20largest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20reiterating%20his%20stance%20on%20the%20need%20for%20reforms%20at%20the%20UN%2C%20he%20said%20the%20countries%20blocking%20the%20reform%20are%20those%20which%20are%20%E2%80%9Cin%20denial%E2%80%9D%20about%20the%20way%20the%20world%20has%20changed%20in%20recent%20decades.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20real%20issue%20is%3A%20how%20do%20we%20refresh%20the%20international%20order%2C%20how%20do%20we%20renovate%20and%20reform%20it%20and%20its%20institutions%3F%20There%20is%20no%20point%20in%20saying%20to%20international%20institutions%3A%20%E2%80%98Do%20your%20job%20better%E2%80%99%20if%20they%20are%20not%20capable%20of%20doing%20so.%20Look%20at%20how%20the%20international%20order%20simply%20collapsed%20during%20a%20historically%20large%20problem%20like%20Covid.%20Every%20country%20acted%20in%20its%20best%20interest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpon%20being%20asked%20if%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20change%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20German%20policy%20given%20that%20India%20is%20trying%20to%20buy%20more%20weapons%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9D%20Germany%20has%20long%20been%20cautious%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20security%20and%20defense.%20In%20contrast%2C%20we%20have%20had%20robust%20cooperation%20with%20France%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20to%20a%20more%20limited%20extent%20with%20Spain%20and%20Italy.%20But%20I%20have%20seen%20a%20development%20in%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20attitude%20in%20recent%20years%3B%20my%20interlocutors%20now%20understand%20that%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20completely%20exclude%20one%20part%20of%20a%20relationship.%20It%20is%20developing%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%20is%20good%20for%20both%20sides.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708518567000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F29133605%2FFzuFHifXoAIWH-o.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Frussia-has-never-hurt-india-interests-jaishankar%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Speaking%20to%20German%20newspaper%20Handelsblatt%2C%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20Munich%20Security%20Conference%2C%20the%20external%20affairs%20minister%20defended%20India's%20decision%20to%20buy%20Russian%20oil%20amid%20Western%20sanctions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Frussia-has-never-hurt-india-interests-jaishankar%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Aadhaar%20Deactivations%20and%20the%20Genealogy%20of%20Cybernetics%20Gone%20Rogue%20in%20India%26nbsp%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21211445%2FAadhaar-1200x560-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20is%20Aadhaar%3F%20An%20identity%20card%2C%20a%20digital%20identity%20project%3F%20Its%20architects%20called%20it%20a%20foundation%2C%20but%20foundation%20to%20what%20%E2%80%93%20a%20digitised%20India%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20genealogy%20of%20the%20Unique%20Identity%20(UID)%20project%20is%20a%20much%20more%20complex%20history%20of%20mathematics%2C%20control%20systems%2C%20geopolitics%20and%20security%20state.%20To%20conclude%20authoritatively%20what%20Aadhaar%20is%20and%20what%20is%20its%20purpose%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20a%20cybernetic%20system%20of%20control%20that%20has%20been%20implemented%20on%20democratic%20systems%20in%20India%20to%20control%20people%20and%20various%20economic%2C%20governance%20and%20social%20systems%20at%20large.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20recent%20developments%20with%20several%20individuals%E2%80%99%20Aadhaar%20being%20de-activated%20has%20created%20a%20flurry%20of%20concerned%20activity%20among%20the%20political%20class%20in%20India%20about%20the%20dangers%20of%20this%20system.%20The%20UID%20project%20allows%20the%20institutions%20in%20India%20to%20control%20various%20aspects%20of%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20life%20by%20using%20their%20information%20to%20make%20decisions%20for%20them.%20These%20decisions%20can%20range%20from%20access%20to%20welfare%20to%20filing%20taxes%20to%20even%20being%20allowed%20to%20vote%20or%20being%20controlled%20throughout%20their%20lifetime%20using%20electronic%20governance%20systems.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20losing%20Aadhaar%20is%20considered%20an%20electronic%20death%20of%20an%20individual%20with%20no%20way%20to%20access%20the%20state%20services%20in%20a%20digital%20society.%20This%20control%20of%20the%20individual%20is%20being%20carried%20out%20by%20the%20state%20through%20a%20cybernetic%20apparatus%20that%20has%20been%20built%20over%20the%20last%20decade%20with%20falsified%20claims%20and%20unconstitutional%20mechanisms.%20It%20is%20important%20to%20understand%20what%20exactly%20this%20system%20is%20before%20one%20pushes%20for%20changes%20to%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20application%20of%20cybernetics%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECybernetics%20is%20a%20science%20of%20feedback%20and%20communication%20part%20of%20systems%20theory%20with%20several%20intersections%20with%20mathematics%2C%20control%20systems%2C%20biology%2C%20psychology%20and%20social%20systems.%20It%20was%20proposed%20by%20celebrated%20mathematician%20Norbert%20Wiener%20in%20his%20book%20%3Cem%3ECybernetics%3A%20or%20Control%20and%20Communication%20in%20the%20Animal%20and%20the%20Machine%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0published%20in%201948.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWiener%20proposed%20this%20new%20theory%20after%20completing%20work%20on%20using%20control%20systems%20to%20help%20the%20US%20Navy%20with%20automatic%20aiming%20and%20firing%20of%20anti-aircraft%20guns%20during%20the%20World%20War%20II.%20He%20later%20questioned%20the%20use%20of%20cybernetics%20on%20humans%20in%20the%20society%20pondering%20the%20social%20questions%20of%20automation%20through%20his%20book%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Human%20Use%20of%20Human%20Beings%3C%2Fem%3E%20published%20in%201950.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20important%20application%20of%20this%20science%20was%20carried%20out%20in%20China%20as%20part%20of%20their%20population%20control%20One-Child%20Policy.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.palladiummag.com%2F2022%2F10%2F17%2Fthe-genealogy-of-chinese-cybernetics%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EChinese%20Cybernetics%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20directly%20influenced%20by%20Wiener%E2%80%99s%20works%2C%20which%20generated%20interest%20among%20Qian%20Xuesen%2C%20the%20famed%20Chinese%20aerospace%20engineer%20and%20cyberneticist%20who%20is%20considered%20as%20the%20father%20of%20the%20Chinese%20missile%20programme.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChinese%20policymakers%20applied%20cybernetics%20to%20optimally%20compute%20its%20ideal%20population%20and%20enforce%20their%20One%20Child%20Policy.%20This%20resulted%20in%20a%20chaos%20of%20un-registered%20%E2%80%9Cblack%20children%E2%80%9D%20across%20rural%20China%2C%20with%20many%20unable%20to%20register%20with%20the%20state%20to%20access%20schools%2C%20medical%20and%20participation%20in%20the%20Chinese%20society%20mediated%20through%20the%20State.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECybernetics%20transformed%20the%20scientific%20community%20and%20made%20several%20scientists%20apply%20these%20principles%20in%20their%20own%20field.%20Cybernetics%20pushed%20a%20new%20wave%20of%20thought%20resulting%20in%20many%20advances%20in%20scientific%20instruments%20and%20pushed%20for%20its%20greatest%20problem%2C%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20cybernetic%20brain%2C%20what%20we%20now%20call%20Artificial%20Intelligence.%20It%20also%20propeled%20new%20ideas%20and%20thought%20experiments%20on%20what%20a%20cyborg%20would%20be%2C%20a%20cybernetic%20organism%20(human%20or%20animal)%20augmented%20and%20controlled%20with%20machines.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Cybernetics%20not%20only%20generated%20interest%20among%20the%20scientific%20community%20but%20also%20within%20sci-fiction%20communities%20generating%20the%20genre%20of%20cyber-punk%20and%20its%20futuristic%20cybernetic%20imaginations%20of%20control.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWiener%E2%80%99s%20India%20visit%20and%20his%20influence%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20seven%20months%20in%201955%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fieeexplore.ieee.org%2Fdocument%2F6397975%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0Wiener%20was%20at%20Indian%20Statistical%20Institute%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(ISI)%20at%20the%20invitation%20of%20Prasanta%20Chandra%20Mahalanobis%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20famed%20statistician%20and%20scientist.%20For%20Mahalanobis%2C%20who%20led%20India%E2%80%99s%20push%20for%20usage%20of%20computers%20in%20planning%2C%20statistics%20was%20not%20just%20a%20field%20of%20mathematics%2C%20but%20a%20technology%20in%20itself.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWiener%20gave%20about%2060%20lectures%20on%20his%20work%2C%20leading%20to%20Indians%20working%20on%20Systems%20Engineering%20and%20its%20application%2C%20which%20helped%20India%20in%20census%20and%20centralised%20planning%20part%20of%20the%20Planning%20Commission.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20mathematician%E2%80%99s%20presence%20in%20India%20pushed%20for%20a%20flurry%20of%20interest%20in%20cybernetics%20among%20Indian%20academics%20at%20the%20ISI%2C%20University%20of%20Delhi%20and%20Council%20of%20Scientific%20and%20Industrial%20Research%20(CSIR)%20in%20the%201960s.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20CSIR%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20research%20and%20development%20organisation%20that%20was%20tasked%20to%20promote%20scientific%20research%2C%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1002%2Fsres.3850070401%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecybernetic%20group%20emerged%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Amitava%20Ghosal%2C%20looking%20into%20problems%20of%20operations%20research%20that%20could%20be%20used%20in%20economic%20planning%20and%20development.%20This%20group%20was%20directly%20influenced%20by%20Stafford%20Beer%2C%20who%20took%20cybernetics%20to%20the%20field%20of%20management%20through%20his%20book%20%3Cem%3ECybernetics%20and%20Management%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Beer%20later%20took%20his%20ideas%20and%20worked%20on%20the%20famous%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F2014%2F10%2F13%2Fplanning-machine%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EProject%20CyberSyn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20in%20Allende%E2%80%99s%20Chile.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20ideas%20of%20cybernetics%20and%20management%20were%20adopted%20within%20the%20Indian%20software%20industry%2C%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20F.C.%20Kohli%20at%20the%20Tata%20Consulting%20Services%20(TCS).%20He%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehelped%20set%20up%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbpb-us-e1.wpmucdn.com%2Fblogs.gwu.edu%2Fdist%2Fd%2F257%2Ffiles%2F2016%2F11%2F2015-JFDP-Abstracts-15i65qh.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESystems%20Engineering%20%26amp%3B%20Cybernetics%20Centre%20(SECC)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20TCS%20at%20Hyderabad%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20P.N.%20Murthy%2C%20a%20professor%20in%20Aeronautics.%20Kohli%20was%20a%20student%20of%20Wiener%20and%20was%20familiar%20with%20his%20work%20at%20MIT.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECybernetics%20and%20the%20Soviet%20Union%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20cybernetics%20programme%20was%20part%20of%20the%20apparatus%20created%20for%20centralised%20planning%20under%20the%20Planning%20Commission%20with%20usage%20of%20computers%20for%20economic%20development%2C%20ideas%20that%20were%20borrowed%20from%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECybernetics%20was%20initially%20considered%20a%20capitalist%20pseudoscience%20under%20Stalin%20and%20was%20ignored%20due%20to%20its%20American%20roots.%20This%20changed%20after%20the%20death%20of%20Stalin%20and%20there%20was%20a%20push%20within%20the%20scientific%20and%20military%20apparatus%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20on%20the%20applications%20of%20cybernetics.%20The%20Soviet%20Union%20quickly%20pushed%20for%20a%20Council%20of%20Cybernetics%20which%20lead%20initiatives%20in%20cybernetics%20while%20competing%20with%20their%20American%20counterparts%2C%20which%20continuously%20kept%20tabs%20on%20what%20was%20happening%20behind%20the%20iron%20curtain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECybernetics%20quickly%20started%20fading%20from%20the%20society%20post%201980s%2C%20with%20the%20evolution%20of%20informatics%20and%20personal%20computing%20across%20the%20world.%20In%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20split%20of%20the%20USSR%2C%20multiple%20arms%20of%20the%20World%20Bank%20and%20western%20multilateral%20institutes%20started%20working%20on%20economic%20development%20of%20Eastern%20European%20countries%20that%20were%20part%20of%20the%20USSR.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Estonia%20became%20a%20%E2%80%98Digital%20Republic%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Institute%20of%20Cybernetics%20that%20was%20setup%20in%20Estonia%20in%20the%201960s%20became%20an%20important%20site%20for%20the%20digital%20age%20in%202000.%20In%201997%2C%20an%20Estonian%20company%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcyber.ee%2Fcompany%2Four-story%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECybernetica%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20established%20by%20the%20people%20who%20were%20part%20of%20the%20Institute%20of%20Cybernetics%20focusing%20on%20delivering%20integrated%20systems%2C%20maritime%20communications%20and%20surveillance%2C%20as%20well%20as%20continuing%20research%20into%20cryptography%20and%20protocols.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECybernetica%20developed%20technologies%20of%20digital%20identities%2C%20digital%20signatures%20and%20platform%20governance%20solutions%20(X-Road)%20for%20Estonia.%20X-%20Road%20became%20the%20backbone%20of%20digital%20governance%20in%20Estonia%20offering%20e-governance%20solutions%20to%20the%20citizens%20of%20Estonia.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20company%20also%20built%20solutions%20for%20electronic%20customs%2C%20tax%20surveillance%20and%20electronic%20voting%20systems%20that%20were%20used%20in%20Estonian%20elections.%20Estonia%20became%20a%20site%20of%20digital%20experiments%20which%20materialised%20cybernetic%20ideas%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Festsjournal.org%2Findex.php%2Fests%2Farticle%2Fview%2F284%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emodern%20information%20society%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20These%20ideas%20that%20evolved%20quickly%20lead%20to%20Estonia%20being%20recognised%20across%20the%20world%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F2017%2F12%2F18%2Festonia-the-digital-republic%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EDigital%20Republic%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Faadhaar-uidai-citizenship-date-of-birth%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Not%20Proof%20of%20Citizenship%20or%20Date%20of%20Birth%E2%80%99%3A%20New%20Aadhaar%20Cards%20Carry%20More%20Prominent%20Disclaimers%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20experiment%20and%20UID%20project%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Estonian%20cybernetic%20dreams%20did%20not%20just%20remain%20in%20Estonia%20but%20travelled%20across%20the%20global%20capital%20networks%20of%20the%20World%20Bank.%20In%202000%2C%20Hyderabad%20emerged%20as%20another%20important%20site%20of%20e-governance%20experiments%2C%20helping%20create%20a%20global%20supply%20chain%20of%20Information%20Technology.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Estonian%20experiments%20quickly%20became%20part%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20information%20technology%20strategy%20under%20former%20IT%20secretary%20J%20Satyanarayana.%20The%20idea%20of%20electronic%20identity%20programme%20became%20a%20part%20of%20the%20national%20task%20force%20on%20IT%20and%20Software%20Development%20setup%20in%201998%2C%20post-Kargil%20War%20review%20committee%E2%80%99s%20recommendation%20of%20an%20electronic%20smart%20card.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELater%2C%20the%20concept%20of%20a%20smart%20card%20took%20the%20shape%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconweb.ucsd.edu%2F~kamurali%2Fpapers%2FOther%2520Writing%2FImplementing%2520a%2520Biometric%2520Payment%2520System%2520(18%2520May%25202013).pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAndhra%20Pradesh%20Smart%20Card%20Project%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%202006.%20As%20a%20part%20of%20of%20this%20project%2C%20biometrics%20in%20payments%20was%20being%20experimented%20in%20the%20southern%20state.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENotably%2C%20these%20ideas%20of%20digital%20identity%2C%20payments%20and%20creation%20of%20a%20digital%20economy%20was%20being%20lobbied%20heavily%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20domestic%20IT%20sector%20and%20were%20given%20a%20concrete%20shape%20for%20governance%20purpose%20through%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.meity.gov.in%2Fdivisions%2Fnational-e-governance-plan%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENational%20E-Governance%20Plan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20advocated%20by%20Satyanarayana%20and%20Nandan%20Nilekani%E2%80%99s%20E-Government%20Foundation%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdarpg.gov.in%2Farc-reports%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E2nd%20Administrative%20Reforms%20Commission%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20UID%20project%2C%20while%20promising%20economic%20development%20through%20the%20centralised%20planning%20part%20of%20the%20Planning%20Commission%2C%20also%20gave%20control%20over%20individuals%20to%20the%20state.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPost%20the%2026%2F11%20Mumbai%20attacks%2C%20t%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehe%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20(MHA)%20wanted%20to%20identify%20and%20control%20every%20individual%20in%20India.%20Aadhaar%20offered%20this%20power%20to%20the%20security%20state%20with%20surveillance%20systems%20that%20were%20being%20built%20as%20part%20of%20the%20policing%20systems%20around%20it%20like%20NATGRID%2C%20CCTNS%2C%20GSTN%20and%20other%20surveillance%20infrastructures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fsecurity-bug-in-mca-portal-leaked-aadhaar-based-kyc-details-of-indias-top-industrialists%5C%22%3ESecurity%20Bug%20in%20MCA%20Portal%20Leaked%20Aadhaar-Based%20KYC%20Details%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Top%20Industrialists%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ERight%20to%20Privacy%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20tussle%20between%20the%20Planning%20Commission%20and%20MHA%20on%20who%20gets%20to%20implement%20Aadhaar%20resulted%20in%20a%20split%20of%20how%20the%20UID%20project%20can%20be%20implemented%20in%20India.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20MHA%20was%20allowed%20to%20collect%20biometrics%20in%20border%20states%2C%20while%20the%20Unique%20Identification%20Authority%20of%20India%20(UIDAI)%20was%20allowed%20to%20issue%20Aadhaar%20within%20mainland%20states%20in%20India.%20These%20differences%20between%20economic%20arms%20and%20the%20security%20state%20have%20come%20to%20an%20end%20post%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20on%20Aadhaar%2C%20with%20increased%20cooperation%20among%20the%20UIDAI%20and%20the%20MHA.%20This%20is%20visible%20with%20the%20recent%20de-activation%20of%20Aadhaar%20numbers%20of%20people%20in%20Assam%20and%20across%20India%20being%20carried%20out%20by%20UIDAI%20at%20the%20request%20of%20various%20policing%20departments%20and%20foreign%20tribunals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20increased%20co-operation%20between%20capital%20and%20state%20apparatus%20is%20helping%20provide%20more%20control%20over%20individuals%20using%20applications%20of%20cybernetics%20(control%20systems).%20The%20forced%20implementation%20of%20Aadhaar%20was%20opposed%20by%20Indian%20activists%20in%20the%20court%20as%20they%20questioned%20that%20the%20project%20was%20against%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy.%20But%20these%20rights%20have%20not%20been%20embedded%20into%20the%20control%20systems%2C%20which%20continue%20to%20remain%20the%20same%20way%20with%20no%20changes%20in%20its%20design%20due%20to%20the%20interests%20of%20economic%20actors%20who%20opposed%20privacy%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20recent%20evolutions%20in%20surveillance%20capitalism.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Aadhaar%20project%20thus%20became%20an%20instrument%20of%20control%20that%20can%20be%20used%20by%20the%20government%20to%20control%20individuals.%20The%20continuous%20push%20by%20the%20state%20to%20update%20details%20by%20standing%20in%20queues%2C%20gives%20the%20state%20more%20control%20over%20its%20citizens.%20Shonini%20Sengupta%2C%20calls%20this%20process%20the%20creation%20of%20an%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fthe-enumerative-indian-state-and-the-ideal-cyborg%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIdeal%20Cyborg%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20Indian%20state%2C%20where%20the%20state%20has%20complete%20control%20over%20the%20cyborgs%20(Indians%20in%20this%20case).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20Project%20CybernSyn%2C%20Stafford%20Beer%20was%20thinking%20about%20how%20to%20design%20cybernetics%20systems%20with%20freedoms%20in%20mind.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20Indian%20cybernetic%20systems%2C%20they%20have%20been%20designed%20with%20the%20need%20to%20control%20the%20populations.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20long%20as%20the%20design%20does%20not%20change%2C%20these%20systems%20will%20promote%20control%20over%20us%20to%20whoever%20has%20the%20switch%20to%20turn%20them%20off.%20Nilekani%20and%20the%20%3Cem%3EKormangala%20Boys%3C%2Fem%3E%20who%20retain%20the%20power%20to%20design%20these%20systems%20along%20with%20the%20bureaucratic%20apparatus%20that%20promotes%20them%2C%20continue%20to%20hold%20the%20switches%20presently.%20There%20is%20a%20need%20to%20reverse%20this%20relationship%20to%20take%20control%20back%20by%20citizens%20over%20their%20digital%20lives%20that%20are%20being%20driven%20by%20broken%20codes%20written%20by%20unaccountable%20individuals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fskodali%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESrinivas%20Kodali%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20researcher%20on%20digitisation%20and%20a%20hacktivist.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708517262000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21211445%2FAadhaar-1200x560-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Faadhaar-deactivations-and-the-genealogy-of-cybernetics-gone-rogue-in-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20recent%20developments%20with%20several%20individuals'%20Aadhaar%20being%20de-activated%20has%20created%20a%20flurry%20of%20concerned%20activity%20among%20the%20political%20class%20in%20India%20about%20the%20dangers%20of%20this%20system.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Faadhaar-deactivations-and-the-genealogy-of-cybernetics-gone-rogue-in-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mystery%20over%20whales'%20singing%20uncovered%20by%20study%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708516140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F02%2F768x432%2Fskynews-whale-whale-song_6463822.jpg%3F20240221133226%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fmystery-over-whales-singing-uncovered-by-study-13077004%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Baleen%20whales%20have%20long%20been%20thought%20to%20sing%20to%20each%20other%20in%20a%20way%20scientists%20couldn't%20identify%20-%20but%20new%20research%20has%20uncovered%20how%20the%20world's%20largest%20mammals%20communicate.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A98%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fmystery-over-whales-singing-uncovered-by-study-13077004%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fmystery-over-whales-singing-uncovered-by-study-13077004%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fmystery-over-whales-singing-uncovered-by-study-13077004%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22J%26amp%3BK%3A%20HC%20Grants%20'Final%20Opportunity'%20to%20Admin%20to%20Respond%20to%20Mirwaiz's%20Plea%20on%20'Illegal%20Confinement'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F22212959%2FThe-Wire-16.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20high%20court%20has%20granted%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20administration%20%E2%80%9Clast%20and%20final%20opportunity%E2%80%9D%20to%20respond%20to%20a%20habeas%20corpus%20petition%20challenging%20the%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20confinement%E2%80%9D%20of%20All%20Parties%20Hurriyat%20Conference%20chairman%2C%20Mirwaiz%20Umar%20Farooq.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20moderate%20Hurriyat%20chairman%20had%20approached%20the%20court%20in%20September%20last%20year%20to%20challenge%20his%20%E2%80%9Carbitrary%20and%20illegal%E2%80%9D%20detention%20after%20August%205%2C%202019%2C%20when%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20was%20bifurcated%20and%20downgraded%20into%20a%20union%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20single%20judge%20Bench%20of%20Justice%20Wasim%20Sadiq%20Nargal%20observed%20on%20Monday%20(February%2019)%20that%20the%20court%20had%20granted%20time%20till%20February%202%20for%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20senior%20additional%20Advocate%20General%2C%20Mohsin%20Qadri%2C%20to%20file%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20objections%20to%20Mirwaiz%E2%80%99s%20petition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20that%20it%20was%20taking%20up%20the%20matter%20%E2%80%9Creluctantly%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cout%20of%20turn%E2%80%9D%20as%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20administration%20had%20not%20responded%20to%20the%20petition%20so%20far.%20%E2%80%9COne%20week%E2%80%99s%20time%20as%20prayed%20for%20is%20granted%20for%20doing%20the%20needful%2C%20which%20however%2C%20shall%20be%20the%20last%20and%20final%20opportunity%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20noted%2C%20while%20listing%20the%20matter%20for%20hearing%20on%20March%206.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20made%20clear%2C%20if%20reply%20is%20not%20filed%2C%20then%20the%20matter%20will%20be%20heard%20on%20the%20next%20date%20of%20hearing%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20and%20Mirwaiz%E2%80%99s%20counsel%20Nazir%20Ahmad%20Ronga%20said%20that%20he%20had%20sought%20directions%20for%20Mirwaiz%E2%80%99s%20release%20and%20urged%20the%20court%20for%20%E2%80%9Cnon-interference%20with%20his%20personal%20liberty%20by%20the%20state%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20sought%20restoration%20of%20the%20rights%20guaranteed%20by%20the%20constitution%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ronga%20told%C2%A0%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMirwaiz%20was%20allowed%20to%20deliver%20his%20first%20sermon%20in%20more%20than%20four%20years%20on%20September%2022%20last%20year%20after%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20administration%20lifted%20the%20curbs%20on%20his%20Srinagar%20residence%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Jamia%20Masjid%2C%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20mosque%2C%20where%20the%20moderate%20Hurriyat%20leader%20delivers%20sermons%20on%20Fridays%20and%20other%20important%20days%20in%20the%20Islamic%20calendar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20development%20came%20a%20week%20after%20the%20high%20court%20directed%20the%20state%20to%20file%20objections%20within%20four%20weeks%20to%20Mirwaiz%E2%80%99s%20habeas%20corpus%20petition%20which%20has%20alleged%20that%20the%20Hurriyat%20leader%20was%20subjected%20to%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20confinement%20in%20a%20most%20unjustified%20and%20illegal%20manner%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20curbs%20were%20reimposed%20soon%20afterwards%2C%20reportedly%20to%20prevent%20anti-Israel%20and%20pro-Palestine%20protests%20at%20the%20historical%20mosque%20which%20was%20an%20epicentre%20of%20anti-India%20and%20pro-freedom%20sentiment%20before%20authorities%20clamped%20down%20on%20protesters%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Article%20370%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurbs%20also%20returned%20to%20Mirwaiz%E2%80%99s%20house%20in%20the%20Nigeen%20locality%20of%20Srinagar%20and%20he%20was%20allegedly%20stopped%20from%20praying%20at%20the%20mosque%20afterwards.%20An%20aide%20of%20Mirwaiz%20said%20that%20he%20was%20allowed%20to%20attend%20three%20consecutive%20Friday%20congregations%20in%20Jamia%20masjid%20following%20the%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20then%20he%20has%20been%20prevented%20from%20going%20to%20Jamia%20Masjid%20on%20Fridays%20or%20addressing%20the%20faithful%20in%20any%20other%20mosque%20or%20religious%20congregations%20as%20the%20Mirwaiz.%20Whenever%20we%20approached%20the%20authorities%2C%20they%20have%20dilly%20dallied%20on%20the%20response%2C%20saying%20they%20will%20check%20with%20their%20higher%20ups%20and%20get%20back%2C%20which%20they%20never%20do%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aide%20said%20that%20the%20Hurriyat%20leader%20has%20been%20allowed%20to%20attend%20family%20emergencies%20or%20social%20functions.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20these%20visits%20have%20been%20few%20and%20far%20between.%20We%20have%20to%20seek%20permission%20from%20the%20local%20police%2024%20hours%20in%20advance%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20aide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20moderate%20Hurriyat%20leader%20also%20recently%20visited%20the%20national%20capital%20reportedly%20due%20to%20some%20%E2%80%9Cfamily%20reasons%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20one%20had%20a%20problem%20with%20him%20going%20to%20New%20Delhi.%20They%20are%20happy%20to%20see%20him%20out%20of%20Kashmir%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%20said%20the%20aide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20official%20of%20Anjuman%20Auqaf%20Jama%20Masjid%20(AAJM)%2C%20the%20managing%20body%20of%20the%20historical%20mosque%2C%20said%20that%20the%20authorities%20stopped%20Mirwaiz%20from%20attending%20the%20recent%20Shab-e-Mehraj%20prayers%20which%20commemorates%20the%20mystical%20flight%20of%20Prophet%20Mohammad%2C%20Islam%E2%80%99s%20most-revered%20prophet%2C%20to%20the%20heaven.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20the%20holy%20month%20of%20Ramzan%20is%20approaching%20when%20there%20are%20multiple%20religious%20events%20and%20congregations%20planned%20for%20Mirwaiz%2C%20this%20approach%20of%20the%20authorities%20is%20concerning%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20AAJM%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20chief%20cleric%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20Mirwaiz%20used%20to%20preside%20over%20matters%20of%20Islamic%20jurisprudence%20in%20Srinagar%2C%20besides%20leading%20the%20Friday%20prayers%20at%20Jamia%20Masjid%20in%20downtown%20Srinagar%E2%80%99s%20Nowhatta%20which%20hosts%20the%20biggest%20congregational%20prayers%20on%20important%20religious%20days%2C%20and%20other%20religious%20functions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20Manoj%20Sinha%20has%20claimed%20that%20Mirwaiz%20was%20%E2%80%9Cfree%20to%20go%20wherever%20he%20wishes%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20Hurriyat%20leader%2C%20who%20was%20part%20of%20the%20Track-2%20dialogue%20between%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Islamabad%20on%20Kashmir%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%20he%20was%20put%20under%20house%20arrest%20%E2%80%9Cillegally%20without%20serving%20of%20any%20order%20of%20detention%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20has%20not%20been%20even%20informed%20as%20to%20why%20he%20has%20been%20detained%20nor%20has%20any%20ground%20of%20detention%20been%20provided%20to%20him%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20petition%20filed%20in%20the%20high%20court%2C%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708516113000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F22212959%2FThe-Wire-16.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjk-hc-grants-final-opportunity-to-admin-to-respond-to-mirwaizs-plea-on-illegal-confinement%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Granting%20a%20week's%20time%20to%20the%20authorities%20to%20file%20their%20response%2C%20Justice%20Wasim%20Sadiq%20Nargal%20scheduled%20the%20next%20hearing%20on%20Mirwaiz%20Umar%20Farooq's%20habeas%20corpus%20petition%20on%20March%206.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjk-hc-grants